150 should be enough. Sometimes  the defaults of some file systems are
too low, like 20 or 25 buffers, this can get you into trouble...
 
> I have a question about imperfect frame updating during intro animation is
> playing: Sometimes video looks like MJPG compression is too big so from time
> to time appears a lots of 'blocks' over the screen. Is it because my CDRom is
> slow or I need to upgrade to CGX4.2? Will it improve video playing quality?

Well, the  frames are delta-compressed  (IIRC with key  frames), which
means  that only  the  difference between  two  consecutive frames  is
stored in the file. If it misses one frame because it could not decode
it in time, this delta (call it a "patch") is not applied to the frame
onscreen, so up  to the next keyframe (or major  redraw) the screen is
mangled. It does this to keep the audio in sync...

