On Wed, 23 Aug 2000, Andrew Barker wrote:

> If we get a Mediator PCI and lob a Voodoo 3dfx card in, will the
> MiniGL driver work with it in any way, or was the MiniGL driver a
> stipped version especially for
> permedia 2 cards ?

MiniGL is a stripped down OpenGL implementation. It has nothing to do 
with Permedia2 (in fact it also works nicely on ViRGE cards), it uses 
Warp3D and will therefore also use a Voodoo board. 

> Obviously it won't use the 3dfx functions, but open gl should work,
> shouldn't it ?

What are 3dfx functions? It will use whatever there is on the Warp3D 
side. Of course this does not include multitexturing since Warp3D does 
not offer this at the moment because of lack of opportunity, but we 
plan on fixing this. However, 3dfx cards are not really a good model 
implementation because there are significant differences. We'll have to 
see.

> Have you guys had any experiences of a 3dfx or similar card on the
> Amiga, via beta testing of the PCI bridge/cards or anything ?

Unfortunately the Mediator is the first of its kind, so the answer is 
no (for the Amiga). But we're also working on Mac, Linux and Windows... 

