> That sounds impressive. A 3D engine that can scale to the hardware
> and still look good is an impressive thing indeed.

Yes, actually LithTech has a lot to offer, like model LOD which is IIRC 
not in the Quake2 engine. LithTech also has the ability to switch off 
lightmapping, and if you are not able to compare the lightmapped 
version with the gouraud shaded view, it will be hard to spot the 
difference. Of course, gouraud shading always has the disadvantage of 
not catching highlights and shadows if they don't touch the vertices, 
and its not invariant towards the view angle, so you might see a bit of 
jumping, but overall this will definately make a difference on the 
Permedia2 speedwise...


